IGridElementCreator, IGridJobCreator
public class GridJobCreator
extends AbstractGridJobCreator

GridJobCreator create grid job. This is middleware independent. Grid job contains of GridJobID, IGridJobDescription and GridJobStatus. And those three components can be middleware dependent.

canCreate

public boolean canCreate(java.lang.Class<? extends IGridElement> elementType)
Description copied from interface: IGridElementCreator
Ask this creator if it is able to create elements of the specified type. If this methods returns true the element type will be remembered until another call of any of the canCreate(...) methods. This element type can afterwards retrieved with the IGridElementCreator.getObject() method.

Parameters:
elementType - The type of the element that should be created.
Returns:
True if this element creator is potentially able to create an element of the specified type.

Create an element and set it to be a child of the specified IGridContainer. The element is created from the object that is returned by the IGridElementCreator.getObject() method. If the creation fails a GridModelException will be thrown.
